1.name: urgent
1.description: Indicates a task or issue requiring immediate attention and resolution.

2.name: bug
2.description: Marks a defect or error in the software or system that needs to be fixed.

3.name: feature
3.description: Designates a new functionality or enhancement to be added to the product.

4.name: documentation
4.description: Categorizes tasks or content related to creating, updating, or reviewing documentation.

5.name: api
5.description: Relates to tasks, issues, or discussions concerning Application Programming Interfaces.

6.name: frontend
6.description: Applies to work on the user interface and client-side development.

7.name: backend
7.description: Pertains to server-side development, databases, and application logic.

8.name: security
8.description: Highlights issues or tasks related to system security, vulnerabilities, or compliance.

9.name: performance
9.description: Identifies tasks focused on improving speed, efficiency, and resource utilization.

10.name: ui
10.description: Refers to design and implementation aspects of the User Interface.

11.name: ux
11.description: Covers tasks related to User Experience design, research, and usability.

12.name: testing
12.description: Used for tasks involving quality assurance, test case creation, or execution.

13.name: deployment
13.description: Marks activities related to releasing software to production or staging environments.

14.name: review
14.description: Designates content or code that requires a formal review process.

15.name: approved
15.description: Indicates that an item, proposal, or change has received official approval.

16.name: draft
16.description: Marks content or work that is in progress and not yet finalized.

17.name: archived
17.description: Used for items that are no longer active but kept for historical reference.

18.name: public
18.description: Designates content or features accessible to all users or the general public.

19.name: private
19.description: Indicates content or features restricted to specific internal users or groups.

20.name: internal
20.description: Applies to internal-facing documentation, tools, or processes for employees only.

21.name: external
21.description: Used for content or features intended for external stakeholders or customers.

22.name: deprecated
22.description: Marks features, APIs, or content that are outdated and will be removed in the future.

23.name: new
23.description: Highlights recently added items, features, or content.

24.name: updated
24.description: Indicates that an item, document, or feature has been recently modified.

25.name: hotfix
25.description: Used for urgent bug fixes deployed quickly to production.

26.name: low-priority
26.description: Designates tasks or issues that can be addressed at a later time.

27.name: high-priority
27.description: Marks tasks or issues that are critical and need to be completed soon.

28.name: optimization
28.description: Focuses on improving efficiency, resource use, or overall system performance.

29.name: refactor
29.description: Indicates code restructuring or redesign to improve maintainability without changing external behavior.

30.name: design
30.description: Pertains to visual, architectural, or functional design tasks.

31.name: content
31.description: Categorizes tasks related to text, media, or information management.

32.name: workflow
32.description: Refers to tasks concerning process automation, improvement, or definition.

33.name: integration
33.description: Used for tasks involving connecting different systems or modules.

34.name: experimental
34.description: Designates features or projects that are in an exploratory or proof-of-concept phase.

35.name: stable
35.description: Indicates a version or feature that is robust, reliable, and production-ready.

36.name: release
36.description: Pertains to activities leading up to and including a software release.

37.name: alpha
37.description: Marks a very early, often internal, version of a product or feature for initial testing.

38.name: beta
38.description: Designates a pre-release version for external testing and feedback.

39.name: candidate
39.description: Identifies a version or item that is being considered for final release or approval.

40.name: final
40.description: Indicates the definitive and approved version of a document, design, or product.

41.name: support
41.description: Relates to customer assistance, troubleshooting, or help desk activities.

42.name: customer
42.description: Highlights tasks or issues directly impacting or originating from customers.

43.name: partner
43.description: Used for tasks or collaborations involving external partners.

44.name: learning
44.description: Categorizes resources or tasks related to skill development and knowledge acquisition.

45.name: training
45.description: Applies to materials or sessions designed for educating users or employees.

46.name: research
46.description: Designates tasks involving investigation, data gathering, or exploratory studies.

47.name: analysis
47.description: Used for tasks involving data interpretation, problem breakdown, or solution evaluation.

48.name: planning
48.description: Covers activities related to strategizing, scheduling, and resource allocation.

49.name: roadmap
49.description: Indicates items related to product or project future direction and strategic initiatives.

50.name: idea
50.description: Marks initial concepts or suggestions that require further exploration.
